this really great kind

00:41:28.870 --> 00:41:35.930
of sonic culture toolkit that
we work to parse sound culture,

00:41:35.930 --> 00:41:38.500
but we also have some
tricks to make it work

00:41:38.500 --> 00:41:42.150
for moving image culture as well.

00:41:42.150 --> 00:41:45.680
So, our goals.

00:41:45.680 --> 00:41:48.050
Advocate for digitization.

00:41:48.050 --> 00:41:50.870
And, all archivists know
that it's a water wheel.

00:41:50.870 --> 00:41:53.560
Once you, it's not digitize
and you're done, right?

00:41:53.560 --> 00:41:56.090
It's digitize and then migrate.

00:41:56.090 --> 00:41:59.750
But, there are a lot of people
working on those challenges.

00:41:59.750 --> 00:42:02.440
Work to develop a scholarly
secure tier

00:42:02.440 --> 00:42:04.130
of access to online collections.

00:42:04.130 --> 00:42:07.700
The time is now for this,
and there's a lot of interest

00:42:07.700 --> 00:42:09.060
in trying to move forward.

00:42:09.060 --> 00:42:13.860
And, we would love for people to
get together and make that happen.

00:42:13.860 --> 00:42:16.700
Help to drive 21st century
scholarship, raise awareness

00:42:16.700 --> 00:42:21.660
about the endangered status,
get some new pedagogy.

00:42:21.660 --> 00:42:25.580
Get scholars to recognize that they
have an obligation to create search

00:42:25.580 --> 00:42:29.540
and discoverability metadata
in their scholarship.

00:42:29.540 --> 00:42:31.830
Engage in this incredible dialectic

00:42:31.830 --> 00:42:34.100
between close reading
and distant reading.

00:42:34.100 --> 00:42:37.200
The arts and humanities,
all about close reading.

00:42:37.200 --> 00:42:41.460
Computational studies,
all about scale, you know.

00:42:41.460 --> 00:42:44.470
That's literally a dialectic,
and we can learn from that.

00:42:44.470 --> 00:42:47.790
We can really move the conversation
and develop new approaches

00:42:47.790 --> 00:42:50.140
that enable crowdsourcing.

